The paper discusses the use of assurance cases for Scientific Computing Software (SCS), which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and computational engineering (cs.CE) categories. The paper also mentions concerns about the validity of Medical Imaging Applications (MIA), which could fall under the computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) categories. Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of producing evidence that can be verified/replicated, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.MS) category.
